environmental effects there,

00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:10.030
one version of it being
this whole new field,

00:05:10.030 --> 00:05:13.970
fetal origins of adult disease,
the fact that early events--

00:05:13.970 --> 00:05:17.990
fetal environmental events--
can have lifelong consequences,

00:05:17.990 --> 00:05:20.470
even multigenerational,
as we saw.

00:05:20.470 --> 00:05:23.250
And people are understanding
the nuts and bolts

00:05:23.250 --> 00:05:26.180
of how that might work,
that epigenetic stuff.

00:05:26.180 --> 00:05:30.430
So we saw that as one--
a very subtle realm

00:05:30.430 --> 00:05:32.420
of environment slipping in.

00:05:32.420 --> 00:05:35.500
And we also saw examples
where "environment" could

00:05:35.500 --> 00:05:37.720
be occurring within
an hour of birth,

00:05:37.720 --> 00:05:39.570
and where environment
is occurring

00:05:39.570 --> 00:05:43.070
despite seemingly like similar
things, like the number of math

00:05:43.070 --> 00:05:46.430
classes you take-- environment
being very critical.

00:05:46.430 --> 00:05:49.660
What we also saw, just to
make life a whole lot messier

00:05:49.660 --> 00:05:51.860
and more complicated,
was violating

00:05:51.860 --> 00:05:54.000
the rule we have all
known since infancy,

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:58.560
which is you get equal genetic
input from each parent.

00:05:58.560 --> 00:06:01.850
The business about mitochondria
coming from your mother--

00:06:01.850 --> 00:06:05.880
the business about, as we
saw, more subtle version--

00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:08.910
the same equal input
of genes, perhaps,

00:06:08.910 --> 00:06:11.570
but the regulatory
control is much more

00:06:11.570 --> 00:06:15.850
coming from the mother by way
of the transcription factors,

00:06:15.850 --> 00:06:18.320
all of that and the
cytosol of the egg,

00:06:18.320 --> 00:06:21.740
sperm having nothing interesting
going on from a cell biology

00:06:21.740 --> 00:06:23.730
level, the egg
having all of this.

00:06:23.730 --> 00:06:26.340
And where you can even
get something as nutty

00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:31.260
as inheritance of an acquired
trait, Lamarckian evolution.

