01:17:44.020 --> 01:17:46.850
you have less social attachment.

01:17:46.850 --> 01:17:50.090
There's a whole psychology
of how you measure that.

01:17:50.090 --> 01:17:51.130
And God knows why.

01:17:51.130 --> 01:17:54.640
It's associated with
less social attachment

01:17:54.640 --> 01:17:57.700
if, and only if,
you got brought up

01:17:57.700 --> 01:18:01.030
by a mother who was
cold and withdrawn.

01:18:01.030 --> 01:18:03.720
There is once again
a "it depends."

01:18:03.720 --> 01:18:06.690
My looking at that, it's
nowhere near as clean as this.

01:18:06.690 --> 01:18:09.210
But it's the same
sort of theme again.

01:18:09.210 --> 01:18:10.940
Another example of it.

01:18:10.940 --> 01:18:14.160
There's another
gene called FAD2.

01:18:14.160 --> 01:18:16.120
And don't even ask me
what it stands for.

01:18:16.120 --> 01:18:20.230
But which version
of the gene you have

01:18:20.230 --> 01:18:24.006
has some predictability
over your IQ.

01:18:24.006 --> 01:18:25.130
That's kind of interesting.

01:18:25.130 --> 01:18:27.690
It's not a big effect, but
nonetheless it is demonstrable.

01:18:27.690 --> 01:18:30.800
Which version of the gene
you have has some control,

01:18:30.800 --> 01:18:33.100
but there's a "it depends."

01:18:33.100 --> 01:18:35.890
Which version of
that gene you have

01:18:35.890 --> 01:18:40.760
has something to do with IQ
if and only if something.

01:18:40.760 --> 01:18:43.880
Let me tell you what
this FAD2 is involved in.

01:18:43.880 --> 01:18:48.520
It is involved in
carbohydrate metabolism.

01:18:48.520 --> 01:18:52.130
Carbohydrates-- carbs,
carbohydrate metabolism-- it

01:18:52.130 --> 01:18:54.690
codes for some enzyme
that breaks down

01:18:54.690 --> 01:18:57.850
carbohydrates and no
doubt, some certain kind.

01:18:57.850 --> 01:18:58.730
OK.

01:18:58.730 --> 01:19:00.180
What's going on here?

01:19:00.180 --> 01:19:01.770
You've got two
different versions

01:19:01.770 --> 01:19:05.330
of a gene that break
down carbohydrates,

01:19:05.330 --> 01:19:06.850
and you've got one version.

01:19:06.850 --> 01:19:10.310
And on the average, you'll
have a higher IQ if and only

01:19:10.310 --> 01:19:12.770
if some environmental
thing was happening.

01:19:12.770 --> 01:19:15.690
Any guesses what that
environmental thing might be?

01:19:20.180 --> 01:19:21.680
High carbohydrate diet.

01:19:21.680 --> 01:19:23.540
High carbohydrate diet, OK.

01:19:23.540 --> 01:19:25.970
That makes tons of
sense, yes indeed.

01:19:25.970 --> 01:19:27.700
That winds up being relevant.

01:19:27.700 --> 01:19:30.010
Remember, you're
now-- not remember,

01:19:30.010 --> 01:19:31.520
because I didn't
say it already--

01:19:31.520 --> 01:19:33.270
but you're looking
at IQ in kids.

01:19:33.270 --> 01:19:36.760
So you're looking now
at carbohydrate stuff

01:19:36.760 --> 01:19:38.060
going on early in life.

01:19:38.060 --> 01:19:39.850
So frame it in that context.

01:19:39.850 --> 01:19:41.800
So, we've got a start
of an answer here.

01:19:41.800 --> 01:19:43.500
So what else could be happening?

01:19:43.500 --> 01:19:46.620
If and only if the
version you have

01:19:46.620 --> 01:19:50.430
of this gene that's involved
in breaking down carbohydrates,

01:19:50.430 --> 01:19:52.990
translating into
how you're dealing

01:19:52.990 --> 01:19:55.090
with the amount of
carbohydrates in your diet,

01:19:55.090 --> 01:19:58.970
gets you a different IQ
with an if and only if.

01:19:58.970 --> 01:20:01.050
What would the if
and only if be?

01:20:01.050 --> 01:20:03.830
Build on that comment there.

01:20:03.830 --> 01:20:05.206
What else could it be?

01:20:09.800 --> 01:20:12.790
OK, I'm not even going to look.

